    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Shooting toys, originally consisting of a tube made from hollowed elder branches or wood used to shoot elderberries, wads of paper, or cork powered by a sudden exhalation of breath. PVC, copper, or other materials may be used for the tube. For weapons using the same method of propulsion, use 'blowpipes.'</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
